was 729 in the apriljune period meaning a typical renter family 
with wage earners between 25 and 44 years old had 729 percent of 
the income needed to qualify for financing to buy a typical starter 
home 
the index measured 73 during the previous quarter the realtors 
composite index measuring the affordability of all buyers of 
existing homes was 104 during the second quarter down from 1043 
from january through march 
the median income of a firsttime homebuyer rose 245 to 23368 
in the second quarter the median income means half of the buyers 
earn more half less 
