<TEXT>
us and un officials said monday there 
was no contradiction between the united nations resolution that 
imposed a trade embargo against iraq and president bushs statement 
that food be included in american quarantine efforts 
iraq roundly condemned internationally for its aug 2 invasion 
of neighboring kuwait imports threequarters of its food for its 
17 million residents 
both the un embargo against iraq and the us quarantine 
include all foodstuffs and grain shipments except in cases of 
distress and humanitarian aid un and us officials said monday 
speaking on condition of anonymity 
the officials emphasized there was no contradiction between the 
un resolution adopted aug 6 and bushs statement sunday that 
food would be included in quarantine efforts 
the un resolution only exempts food from the embargo in 
humanitarian circumstances it bars the import of food to build 
up iraqi stocks and allows it only when there is serious need 
bush said that food would be covered in us efforts to 
interdict commercial vessels bound for iraq but added that in some 
cases of severe deprivation and need there might be exemptions 
the language in the convoluted un resolution has given rise to 
confusion about inclusion or exclusion of food and un officials 
declined to interpret the language saying the resolution stands 
for itself 
but privately they said the resolution imposes an embargo on all 
foodstuffs except in dire circumstances canada reportedly ordered 
a grain vessel bound for iraq to return recently diplomats said 
section c of the un resolution says that un member states 
should prevent 
the sale or supply by their nationals or from their 
territories or using their flag vessels of any commodities or 
products including weapons or any other military equipment 
whether or note originating in their territories but not including 
supplies intended strictly for medical purposes and in 
humanitarian circumstances foodstuffs to any person or body in 
iraq or kuwait or to any person or body for the purposes of any 
business carried on in or operated from iraq or kuwait and any 
activities by their nationals or in their territories which promote 
or are calculated to promte such saleor supply of such commodities 
or products 
the resolution also bans financial dealings with iraq except 
those intended exclusively for medical or humanitarian purposes and 
in humanitarian circumstances foodstuffs 
