suburban coral gables 
at 9 pm edt frans center was near 94 degrees north latitude 
and 563 degrees west longitude or about 330 miles eastsoutheast 
of trinidad tropical stormforce winds of at least 39 mph extended 
175 miles from frans center 
the government of trinidad and tobago which weathered an 
unsuccessful coup attempt by radical black moslems two weeks ago 
issued a tropical storm warning for its territory as well as 
grenada and other nearby islands in the southeastern caribbean 
a tropical storm watch was in effect for several islands to the 
north barbados st vincent and the grenadines said hurricane 
specialist hal gerrish 
the storm was expected to keep to its path and strengthen 
slightly tuesday gerrish said but its progress across the 
atlantic was expected to slow 
the atlantic hurricane season runs from june 1 to november 30th 
