stock trading stranding people in elevators and sending thousands 
home early through trafficsnarled streets 
consolidated edison said power could be out for several days in 
a commercial area of roughly 50 square blocks 
the midday cable fire at a con ed substation spewed plumes of 
black acrid smoke into the air over the southern tip of manhattan 
workers poured out of buildings like the world trade center and 
south street seaport in search of pay phones and cool drinks 
many subway lines and commuter tunnels were stalled or shut 
down thousands walked across the brooklyn bridge and rushhour 
ferry service began early 
