register the countrys first white student union 
spletzer who graduated this spring keeps in touch with kristl 
wiernicki dean of students at temple wiernicki decided that once 
the white student union met school requirements getting an adviser 
and drafting a suitable constitution she was obliged to let it 
register at temple which has 34000 students nearly 25 percent 
are racial minorities 
wiernicki said that after the white student unions initial 
stormy recruitment effort when students of all colors tangled with 
the union in loud public debate it vanished from campus 
she regards the white student union as a passing trend but says 
it was also important not to ignore what spletzer and his 
apparently few comrades were after what spletzer was saying was 
we dont want you to lose sight of us wiernicki adds 
a recent visit to the temple campus seemed to confirm 
wiernickis assessment 
freshmen had scarcely heard of the union older students said it 
hasnt been heard from in a long time 
on the urban campus where every identifiable group seems to 
have its own unofficial corner in the student activities center 
most people see the white union as part of the mosaic 
others called them troublemakers theyre racist pigs said 
josephine chiappetta 20 a business major who is white i feel 
the same way about the black students union 
those who gravitated to temples white union said junior 
michael tilghman are just disturbed that blacks get so much 
financial help and other assistance by starting a white student 
union thats a way to express their anger he said 
on one point tilghman who is black agrees with them however 
affirmative action is an insult to me give me the same as a 
white person 
</TEXT>
