das rheingold deutsche grammophon conducted by james 
levine played by metropolitan opera orchestra 
 
the second installment in the metropolitan operas complete 
recording of wagners ring cycle is a disappointment a distinctly 
routine rheingold 
dont fault the singing or the orchestral playing both are 
firstrate as one would expect rather the problem seems to lie 
with conductor james levine whose reading of the score too often 
falls flat it lacks the fire and energy that made soltis 
recording a classic and rarely conjures up the chambermusic 
effect that distinguished karajans interpretation 
the cast is mostly familiar to anyone who has seen the 
production at the met or who watched the recent television version 
on pbs james morris is a sturdy resonant wotan christa ludwig is 
expressive as fricka his wife siegfried jerusalem is superb as 
loge the wily demigod ekkehard wlaschiha and heinz zednik make a 
strong pair of brother dwarfs alberich and mime birgitta svenden 
