performances heikyung hongs soprano adds luster to the role of 
the lead rhinemaiden woglinde bass kurt moll sings the part of 
the giant fasolt so beautifully he makes him downright sympathetic 
the way the late martti talvela did on the karajan recording 
but the big moments in rheingold are orchestral rather than 
vocal the creationoftheworld opening measures the interludes 
before and after the nibelungen scene with the sound of hammers 
clinking on anvils the brassy entrance of the gods into valhalla 
