want to say anything the picture of the market suddenly 
disappeared and a number of dealers were affected said bruce 
chalfant assistant vice president for information services at 
telerate im sure there are people who are not going to be 
sleeping well there was no close things just stopped 
on the new york merc one of three key world oil markets besides 
london and singapore the price of benchmark west texas 
intermediate crude was up 54 cents to 2677 a barrel when trading 
shut down 
among refined products traded on the exchange wholesale 
homeheating oil rose 244 cents to 7505 cents a gallon and 
wholesale unleaded gasoline rose 335 cents to 8280 cents a gallon 
the exchange said the days trading would be reflected in the 
tally of transactions for tuesday when trading was expected to 
return to normal 
the dow jones industrial average rose 3020 points to 274678 
but the broader market for stocks was mixed and trading was light 
because of the power outage the amex market value index was down 
118 to 33814 before the outage 
prices in the bond market an important barometer of interest 
rates were mixed in light volume as well 
gold was up 830 a troy ounce at 40520 on the new york 
commodity exchange when traded halted the highest price since 
early march and a signal of growing inflation anxiety caused by the 
rise in oil 
the dollar lost value reflecting expectations that higher 
interest rates abroad will make foreign currencies such as the 
german mark and japanese yen worth more 
