<TEXT>
two major airlines announced monday they would cut some domestic 
air fares for a limited time offering the promotion at a time 
major airlines have raised most ticket prices to account for 
sharply higher fuel prices 
eastern airlines announced new discount oneway fares that will 
range from 69 to 139 and cover all easterns 62 us destinations 
from sept 5 through dec 16 the tickets must be purchased by aug 
29 eastern said 
the cheaper fares which will apply only to roundtrip tickets 
with a saturday overnight stay were announced two days before 
easterns scheduled 53 percent hike in its other fares 
like other major airlines eastern is raising most of its fares 
because of the jump in jet fuel prices following the aug 2 
invasion of kuwait by iraq and subsequent speculation of a 
disruption in oil supplies 
the discount fares arent available for travel on nov 21 and 
nov 2526 but the tickets will be refundable eastern said 
separately trans world airlines announced it would cut 
nonrefundable domestic fares in most markets 20 percent or more 
reducing the rate to 158 oneday from new york to st louis for 
example 
trans world spokesman jim faulkner said the company still plans 
to raise international fares by 20 and might consider raising its 
domestic fares in the future if fuel prices do not retreat 
trans worlds cheaper tickets must be purchased between tuesday 
and aug 29 for travel between sept 5 and dec 16 
airlines that have announced fuelrelated fare hikes include 
delta united usair northwest america west midway pan am 
southwest and trump shuttle 
