average gasoline prices dropped more than 3 
cents nationwide this weekend after soaring nearly 18 cents as the 
persian gulf crisis unfolded the american automobile association 
said monday 
aaas national fuel gauge report shows selfserve regular 
unleaded averages 1216 per gallon down 34 cents since friday 
in detroit on monday the average price fell 6 cents to 1184 
per gallon in st louis it fell 6 cents to 1063 per gallon 
and in kansas city it dropped 17 cents to 1121 
in washington motorists were paying 1157 per gallon up 7 
cents since friday the average costs in the capital had dropped 2 
cents between wednesday and friday 
in southern indiana the average price which dropped 5 cents 
overnight friday increased 1 cent monday to 122 per gallon 
mondays survey was based on a spot check of stations nationwide 
by computer petroleum corp of st paul minn the company also 
publishes the national petroleum price index which monitors more 
than 50000 daily wholesale prices in the united states and canada 
the orlandobased aaa is a notforprofit federation of motor 
clubs with nearly 32 million members in the united states and 
canada 
